# Accessibility Constraints

## WCAG Compliance
- Follow WCAG 2.1 Level AA guidelines minimum
- Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible
- Provide sufficient color contrast (4.5:1 for normal text)
- Support screen readers with proper ARIA labels
- Make all content accessible without mouse

## Semantic HTML
- Use proper heading hierarchy (h1, h2, h3...)
- Use semantic HTML5 elements (nav, main, article, aside)
- Provide alt text for all images
- Use labels for all form inputs
- Mark up tables properly with headers

## Keyboard Navigation
- All functionality must be available via keyboard
- Provide visible focus indicators
- Support Tab, Shift+Tab, Enter, Space, Arrow keys
- Implement skip links for navigation
- Avoid keyboard traps

## Screen Reader Support
- Add ARIA labels where semantic HTML isn't sufficient
- Announce dynamic content changes with aria-live
- Provide text alternatives for icon-only buttons
- Test with actual screen readers (NVDA, JAWS, VoiceOver)
- Use aria-describedby for additional context

## Visual Design
- Support text resize up to 200%
- Don't rely on color alone to convey information
- Provide clear error messages
- Ensure sufficient spacing between interactive elements
- Support both light and dark modes

## Testing
- Run automated accessibility tests (axe, pa11y)
- Test with keyboard only
- Test with screen readers
- Include users with disabilities in testing
- Maintain accessibility in all new features
